A soldier identified as Kila Jima fighting Boko Haram insurgents in the North-East has reportedly killed himself. The soldier, a corporal in the Army’s 152 Battalion, Banki, was said to have suddenly cocked his rifle and shot himself in the head. File Photo The incident happened on Saturday. It is not yet clear what led the soldier to kill himself. He was said to have shown some sign of depression before he eventually took his life. SaharaReporters gathered that his body has been deposited at the military mortuary in Maiduguri.



